line_1: We praise and censure with an eye to self;
line_2: When, in discoursing on each mimic elf,

line_1: Unbending austerity, wrapt up in self,
line_2: Is so like a miser when hoarding his pelf.

line_2: CAnst Thou in Dungeons smother up that Pelf

line_1: you might claim a Durchlachen from Witikind's self:
line_2: of gravens new made, tho like me, saucy Elf,

line_1: I've no Envy to Thee, and some Love to my Self:
line_2: Lye, Philo, untouch'd on my peaceable Shelf;

line_1: That teach one to deny one's self,
Or if to see the name of idol self
line_2: Stamp'd on the well-bound quarto, grace the shelf,

line_1: O scepter'd suicide! destroy thy self.
line_2: Nor, draining wasted realms for sordid pelf,

line_1: Cymothoe wrongs her Glaucus, and her self,
line_2: To think I languish for that scaly Elf.
